[thinking] 
[thinking] I’m thinking about the rule that all top-level test classes must be public. It seems like having public support is okay, but I wonder if there's a “one-to-one mapping” issue with dynamic-access report classes and test class files. Nested classes might be less preferred, so maybe having separate files without `$` or `@Test` is better. I should create three public class files and remove top-level support from LoadClassTest. Let’s also consider making the FilteringClassLoader nested.
