I'm considering whether the public API has an overload for LoadClass.action. It seems it's part of a public internal class, but not exactly part of the public API. The rules indicate I should focus on what's available within the public library API. However, I wonder if I could directly use org.hibernate.validator.internal.util.actions.LoadClass instead, but that seems likely to be rejected. So, I'll need to stick to the normal public API path.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_BnEIT2MSGH6y1zmb9yharUM2|fc_0c53adcb8df17cf9016a3bc87105ec8195aaafe0038bcaf501", "name": "bash", "arguments": {"command": "jshell <<'EOF'\nclass CL extends ClassLoader { protected Class<?> loadClass(String n, boolean r) throws ClassNotFoundException { if (n.equals(\"foo.Bar\")) return String.class; return super.loadClass(n,r);} }\ntry { System.out.println(Class.forName(\"foo.Bar\", false, new CL())); } catch (Throwable t) { t.printStackTrace(); }\nEOF", "timeout": 20}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 15716, "output": 2349, "cacheRead": 49152, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 67217, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1782302789536, "responseId": "resp_0c53adcb8df17cf9016a3bc847d3c4819589f02678864a50c0"}}
