[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering ClassLoader behavior**\n\nI'm wondering if a custom ClassLoader can override the loadClass method for \"org.hibernate.validator.NonExisting\" and somehow return a class. For it to work, it seems like that class must have a matching name. The ClassLoader.loadClass specification likely ensures that the VM checks the name. I'm thinking Class.forName probably expects a name match as well. But could a ClassLoader return a class with a different name? I suspect that Class.forName eventually uses loadClass to verify the name, but testing that could lead to complications.\n\n**Exploring API options**\n\nI'm considering whether the public API has an overload for LoadClass.action. It seems it's part of a public internal class, but not exactly part of the public API. The rules indicate I should focus on what's available within the public library API. However, I wonder if I could directly use org.hibernate.validator.internal.util.actions.LoadClass instead, but that seems likely to be rejected. So, I'll need to stick to the normal public API path.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0c53adcb8df17cf9016a3bc8491b2c819599eb9978ea6f828e\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"content\":[],\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABqO8hxNZ2Xk8EhipXMc2GMaUmbWQ5tRngdwsaDP7KOgeQhY_Jh6mMzq-7U5zQETl84H4RUwQOVgPk9oFKzOR8nfNcZTmrSanZCsAmojj09x9f84dE-PcbmPAgsqqRmuayT9lbF8z9nM7pXVutxevqZcx-qLbhweCxXQXn5SBh6tgLVQlMKwvBG7hE0L2tj8syBImtU5K5LcK9qCeiBy2XgMNE_m228LRi2xDztSvRCn2V1FRly-JzxkQu6B2sNQ3Ejeh8Ijtx1CaSZMyaul86xkFK7WbZa64QhVRglkk5VzbijvyIIF1eyKe0HVEysQ1NvALoCUaI1fhu07EhEAoZNj-Y9b6z4dsGfWlYH8LbM4LFn1hqwXfuTeueU7p2NOdloNWz5dBNJxbJ-Y6HbzvD12g9HV6wdrAucDVq7R5eNvN2LxbGH3fpb1uQOoJSnKPAgUw-CVNYHkc2dUCMsRRmloQBLfPEkrTs2mjBm8wOPCarFRKC1c2w4U_8Xx3hiEZg-h-UZVkQpFRbPjlUEuo12dsn02xa74BXHmeYsfX7PHx5r0rm6qBUQuzUd2fYFUxQEp1NE8eFe-fA2gxMoHfk_aOCj2Nuw4lXTjwOLayzSVmcMTUB-dpFzt0wGUbWmyisxjbGcBXTMXJwVnO6CJG4QiB4N9XT_